{
  "stem": "11089.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she had to clean, and clean.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And my mother had to clean.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They brought in dirt and lice and so on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There was no Shabbos without beggars.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But if we had a guest, first of all, you would feel good, because as soon you walked into the house, you had a good-- first of all, the table was beautiful.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Covered, my mother was in a white [NON-ENGLISH], you know, covered.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The children were dressed nice.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the songs, you know, Shalom Aleichem and the Kiddush.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It was something-- it's so-- it was soaked into you-- into-- into your-- into your body, into your system.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "You would have to sing with us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "You would have to eat with us and have a good time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And same as a Shabbat, Special food, [NON-ENGLISH] and fish.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we were blessed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Our village had mineral waters.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Like today, you have seltzer.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "What we had, wells coming out with these waters.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And every family had a balloon, like a bottle, it was called, with that water.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And no matter how much [NON-ENGLISH] you ate or kugel, you drank a glass of that water, you would go to sleep and nothing will happen.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "It was beautiful.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Shabbos, we went for a sleep later on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We kids went to play.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Everybody went to shul.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Not because they were so religious, but there was a custom.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "Everybody must go to shul.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And my father made a custom that every boy, after bar mitzvah, he has to sing one chapter as a [NON-ENGLISH], and writing, you know, like, and going around in circles.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Everybody had to be there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Not because they were so religious, because that was the life as a village.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And then [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And then even for Saturday night we made a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
